{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-05",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_05_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "05 - Advice from a Caterpillar",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.747,
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 244.6,
  "page_end_sec": 487.8,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 244.6,
      "end": 246.34,
      "text": "By the use of this ointment--"
    },
    {
      "start": 246.42,
      "end": 247.44,
      "text": "one shilling the box--"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.72,
      "end": 249.32,
      "text": "Allow me to sell you a couple?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 250.02,
      "end": 250.7,
      "text": "\"You are old,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 250.84,
      "end": 251.42,
      "text": "said the youth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 251.54,
      "end": 254.68,
      "text": "and your jaws are too weak for anything tougher than suet;"
    },
    {
      "start": 255.34,
      "end": 257.84,
      "text": "Yet you finished the goose, with the bones and the beak--"
    },
    {
      "start": 258.02,
      "end": 258.32,
      "text": "Pray,"
    },
    {
      "start": 258.48,
      "end": 260.02,
      "text": "how did you manage to do it?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 260.72,
      "end": 261.26,
      "text": "\"In my youth,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 261.34,
      "end": 262.1,
      "text": "said his father,"
    },
    {
      "start": 262.28,
      "end": 263.34,
      "text": "I took to the law,"
    },
    {
      "start": 263.5,
      "end": 265.34,
      "text": "and argued each case with my wife;"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.12,
      "end": 267.86,
      "text": "And the muscular strength, which it gave"
    },
    {
      "start": 267.86,
      "end": 270.38,
      "text": "to my jaw, has lasted the rest of my life.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 270.98,
      "end": 272.08,
      "text": "\"You are old,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 272.2,
      "end": 272.8,
      "text": "said the youth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.8,
      "end": 276.0,
      "text": "one would hardly suppose that your eye was as steady as ever;"
    },
    {
      "start": 276.24,
      "end": 278.88,
      "text": "Yet you balanced an eel on the end of your nose--"
    },
    {
      "start": 279.18,
      "end": 280.8,
      "text": "What made you so awfully clever?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 281.6,
      "end": 283.32,
      "text": "\"I have answered three questions,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 283.54,
      "end": 284.34,
      "text": "and that is enough,"
    },
    {
      "start": 284.56,
      "end": 285.34,
      "text": "Said his father;"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.52,
      "end": 286.86,
      "text": "\"don't give yourself airs!"
    },
    {
      "start": 287.44,
      "end": 289.78,
      "text": "Do you think I can listen all day to such stuff?"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.18,
      "end": 290.56,
      "text": "Be off,"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.66,
      "end": 291.64,
      "text": "or I'll kick you down stairs!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 294.5,
      "end": 295.78,
      "text": "\"That is not said right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 296.04,
      "end": 297.06,
      "text": "said the Caterpillar."
    },
    {
      "start": 297.96,
      "end": 298.82,
      "text": "\"Not _quite_ right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 298.88,
      "end": 299.32,
      "text": "I'm afraid,"
    },
    {
      "start": 299.5,
      "end": 300.56,
      "text": "said Alice, timidly;"
    },
    {
      "start": 300.98,
      "end": 302.27,
      "text": "Some of the words have got altered."
    },
    {
      "start": 303.04,
      "end": 305.92,
      "text": "\"It is wrong from beginning to end,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 306.3,
      "end": 308.12,
      "text": "said the Caterpillar, decidedly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 308.52,
      "end": 310.4,
      "text": "and there was silence for some minutes."
    },
    {
      "start": 311.44,
      "end": 313.76,
      "text": "The Caterpillar was the first to speak.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 314.76,
      "end": 316.62,
      "text": "\"What size do you want to be?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 316.86,
      "end": 317.52,
      "text": "it asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.34,
      "end": 319.14,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 319.18,
      "end": 320.92,
      "text": "I'm not particular as to size,"
    },
    {
      "start": 321.24,
      "end": 322.34,
      "text": "Alice hastily replied;"
    },
    {
      "start": 323.2,
      "end": 325.58,
      "text": "only one doesn't like changing so often,"
    },
    {
      "start": 325.66,
      "end": 325.94,
      "text": "you know."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.36,
      "end": 328.3,
      "text": "\"I _don't_ know,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 328.62,
      "end": 329.7,
      "text": "said the Caterpillar."
    },
    {
      "start": 332.1,
      "end": 332.88,
      "text": "Alice said nothing:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 333.42,
      "end": 336.5,
      "text": "she had never been so much contradicted in all her life before,"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.66,
      "end": 338.64,
      "text": "and she felt that she was losing her temper."
    },
    {
      "start": 341.3,
      "end": 343.44,
      "text": "\"Are you content now?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 343.86,
      "end": 344.82,
      "text": "said the Caterpillar."
    },
    {
      "start": 345.89,
      "end": 346.44,
      "text": "\"Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 346.5,
      "end": 348.14,
      "text": "I should like to be a _little_ larger,"
    },
    {
      "start": 348.2,
      "end": 348.42,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 348.5,
      "end": 349.3,
      "text": "if you wouldn't mind,"
    },
    {
      "start": 349.5,
      "end": 350.02,
      "text": "said Alice:"
    },
    {
      "start": 350.44,
      "end": 352.6,
      "text": "Three inches is such a wretched height to be."
    },
    {
      "start": 353.68,
      "end": 355.92,
      "text": "\"It is a very good height indeed!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 357.3,
      "end": 358.78,
      "text": "said the Caterpillar angrily,"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.78,
      "end": 360.94,
      "text": "rearing itself upright as it spoke"
    },
    {
      "start": 361.38,
      "end": 362.92,
      "text": "(it was exactly three inches"
    },
    {
      "start": 363.06,
      "end": 363.18,
      "text": "high)."
    },
    {
      "start": 364.64,
      "end": 365.98,
      "text": "\"But I'm not used to it!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 366.0,
      "end": 367.9,
      "text": "pleaded poor Alice in a piteous tone,"
    },
    {
      "start": 368.8,
      "end": 369.72,
      "text": "and she thought to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 370.12,
      "end": 372.94,
      "text": "\"I wish the creatures wouldn't be so easily offended!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 374.432,
      "end": 376.08,
      "text": "\"You'll get used to it in time,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 376.36,
      "end": 377.38,
      "text": "said the Caterpillar,"
    },
    {
      "start": 377.52,
      "end": 379.34,
      "text": "and it put its hookah into its"
    },
    {
      "start": 379.42,
      "end": 380.98,
      "text": "mouth and began smoking again."
    },
    {
      "start": 382.12,
      "end": 385.52,
      "text": "This time Alice waited patiently until it chose to speak again.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 385.99,
      "end": 389.02,
      "text": "In a minute or two the Caterpillar took the hookah out"
    },
    {
      "start": 389.02,
      "end": 391.78,
      "text": "of its mouth and yawned once or twice, and shook itself."
    },
    {
      "start": 392.8,
      "end": 395.84,
      "text": "Then it got down off the mushroom, and crawled away into the grass,"
    },
    {
      "start": 396.1,
      "end": 397.68,
      "text": "merely remarking as it went,"
    },
    {
      "start": 398.5,
      "end": 400.58,
      "text": "\"One side will make you grow taller,"
    },
    {
      "start": 400.78,
      "end": 403.86,
      "text": "and the other side will make you grow shorter."
    },
    {
      "start": 405.46,
      "end": 406.14,
      "text": "\"One side of _what_?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 407.16,
      "end": 408.04,
      "text": "\"The other side of _what_?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 408.12,
      "end": 408.98,
      "text": "thought Alice to herself."
    },
    {
      "start": 410.144,
      "end": 411.02,
      "text": "\"Of the mushroom,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 411.54,
      "end": 412.7,
      "text": "said the Caterpillar,"
    },
    {
      "start": 412.8,
      "end": 414.52,
      "text": "just as if she had asked it aloud."
    },
    {
      "start": 414.96,
      "end": 417.26,
      "text": "and in another moment it was out of sight."
    },
    {
      "start": 419.232,
      "end": 421.7,
      "text": "Alice remained looking thoughtfully at the mushroom for",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 421.7,
      "end": 422.06,
      "text": "a minute,"
    },
    {
      "start": 422.2,
      "end": 424.84,
      "text": "trying to make out which were the two sides of it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 424.9,
      "end": 426.48,
      "text": "and as it was perfectly round,"
    },
    {
      "start": 426.8,
      "end": 428.78,
      "text": "she found this a very difficult question."
    },
    {
      "start": 429.18,
      "end": 429.88,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 430.08,
      "end": 432.92,
      "text": "at last she stretched her arms round it as far as"
    },
    {
      "start": 432.92,
      "end": 433.46,
      "text": "they would go,"
    },
    {
      "start": 433.6,
      "end": 436.24,
      "text": "and broke off a bit of the edge with each hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 437.48,
      "end": 438.4,
      "text": "\"And now which is which?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 438.6,
      "end": 439.02,
      "text": "she said"
    },
    {
      "start": 439.14,
      "end": 439.42,
      "text": "to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 439.94,
      "end": 442.94,
      "text": "and nibbled a little of the right-hand bit to try the effect:"
    },
    {
      "start": 443.78,
      "end": 444.8,
      "text": "the next moment she felt"
    },
    {
      "start": 444.8,
      "end": 446.5,
      "text": "a violent blow underneath her chin:"
    },
    {
      "start": 446.68,
      "end": 447.98,
      "text": "it had struck her foot!"
    },
    {
      "start": 449.3,
      "end": 450.96,
      "text": "She was a good deal frightened by this",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 451.04,
      "end": 451.94,
      "text": "very sudden change,"
    },
    {
      "start": 452.32,
      "end": 454.6,
      "text": "but she felt that there was no time to be lost,"
    },
    {
      "start": 454.82,
      "end": 456.54,
      "text": "and as she was shrinking rapidly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 457.08,
      "end": 459.8,
      "text": "so she set to work at once to eat some of the other bit."
    },
    {
      "start": 460.5,
      "end": 462.22,
      "text": "Her chin was pressed so closely against"
    },
    {
      "start": 462.38,
      "end": 464.84,
      "text": "her foot that there was hardly room to open her mouth;"
    },
    {
      "start": 464.98,
      "end": 467.02,
      "text": "but she did it at last, and managed to"
    },
    {
      "start": 467.16,
      "end": 468.82,
      "text": "swallow a morsel of the left-hand bit."
    },
    {
      "start": 469.64,
      "end": 470.48,
      "text": "\"Come,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 470.68,
      "end": 471.74,
      "text": "my head's free at last!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 471.96,
      "end": 473.08,
      "text": "said Alice in a tone of"
    },
    {
      "start": 473.16,
      "end": 473.32,
      "text": "delight,"
    },
    {
      "start": 473.52,
      "end": 475.88,
      "text": "which changed into alarm in another moment,"
    },
    {
      "start": 476.06,
      "end": 477.86,
      "text": "when she found that her shoulders were"
    },
    {
      "start": 477.96,
      "end": 478.68,
      "text": "nowhere to be found:"
    },
    {
      "start": 479.38,
      "end": 480.18,
      "text": "All she could see,"
    },
    {
      "start": 480.3,
      "end": 481.24,
      "text": "when she looked down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 481.4,
      "end": 483.06,
      "text": "was an immense length of neck,"
    },
    {
      "start": 483.5,
      "end": 485.4,
      "text": "which seemed to rise like a stalk out of a"
    },
    {
      "start": 485.4,
      "end": 487.8,
      "text": "sea of green leaves that lay far below her."
    }
  ]
}